{emoji:"🏺",name:"Rakhigarhi — Largest Harappan Site",location:"Hisar District",desc:"The largest Harappan Civilization site in the Indian subcontinent — larger than Mohenjo-daro and Harappa — with evidence of continuous occupation from 6,500 BCE to 2,000 BCE. Excavations have revealed a grid-planned city, granaries, drainage systems, jewelry workshops, fire altars and pottery. The 2019 DNA study of Rakhigarhi's ancient genome published in Cell is one of the most significant archaeological discoveries in recent history.",fee:["Museum: Paid"]},
